      <context>
         <note id="note_zzj_11z_5gc" type="notice">
            <p>Improper lifting or tiedowns can allow load to shift and cause injury and/or damage.</p>
         </note>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Weight is given on the serial plate.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Use proper rated cables and slings for lifting. Position the
crane for level lift truck lift.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Spreader bar widths should be sufficient to prevent contact
with the lift truck</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Use the tiedown locations provided for lift truck tiedown.</p>
            <p>
               <p>Check the state and local laws governing weight, width, and
              length of a load.</p>
               <p>Contact your Time Lift Truck branch for shipping instructions
              for your lift truck.</p>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
